reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 6, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great Quality, Especially Considering The Price.
reviews.reviewText: These headphones are really great! I wanted some AirPod Maxes (and still do just because) but I'm not trying to pay $500 for some headphones. These Rockpapa E8 headphones are a great alternative, for a way cheaper price. The noise cancellation is pretty good from my experience, most noises are blocked out when using a regular volume. They are also pretty comfortable, but when used for hours on end they can cause irritation to the ears. Another thing I was impressed with was the battery life, I can use these throughout my day for multiple days without having to charge! One thing I can say is that when the battery is low, there will be a pretty annoying interruption around every 2 minutes stating; 'BATTERY LOW'. All in all, these headphones are comfortable, aesthetically pleasing, and have great battery life, I'd definitely recommend! (I also love the cute rockpapa logo, it kinda looks like Bob Ross)

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 25, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Product seems to crush my ears!
reviews.reviewText: While I have been very loyal to the RockPapa brand, my most recent purchase did not seem to be up to the product standards I expected. When the product arrived it was neatly packaged and all parts were in the box. Upon first inspection I noticed that the ear cushion for the left ear had a deep indentation in it from being folded, and even after days of being unfolded the indention is still present. While I typically could overlook this defect I was thrown aback by the fact that (almost instantly) the headphones seemed to tightly squeeze my ears to the point of discomfort. I would recommend that these headphones only be used by those with a small head or really small ears.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 11, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Truly an Amazing product
reviews.reviewText: Considering price point and ease of access, these headphones really exceeded my expectations as someone who is very avid towards music and typically doesn’t cheap out on speakers and headphones. These headphones honestly feel very up to par with big name brands. From the included case, down to the sound of the headphones and their everyday functionality, these headphones are nearly perfect. They’re light, loud, and have great bass on the right settings and volume. They sound amazing, and paired with their comfortable ear muffs, they have amazing noice cancellation. They are also great for travel, they fold small and the case makes them easy to carry around. In terms of aesthetics, they look especially good as someone who has struggled in the past finding an over ear headphone that doesn’t bend and warp, they look great on my head! Would 1000% recommend to anyone consider.
These are great value for money and perfect for the smaller heads. The sound and look are great
